column3: str
Urianger is eager to rejoin Y'shtola.
Speak with Y'shtola at the Drowning Brand.
Survey the area.
Speak with Zero.
Y'shtola, was it?
Ah, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>. We can begin as soon as the others arrive.
Some manner of cactuar attempted to make mischief, but no one came to harm. How did you fare?
With Estinien keeping us safe, we were able to finish repairing the brands without incident!
<UIForeground>F20223</UIForeground>What aid I lend in restoring the brands is insignificant next to that which you and yours must accomplish.<UIForeground>01</UIForeground>

<UIForeground>F20223</UIForeground>When my part is complete, I shall stand apart and observe, as I have ever done. For it was to you that Venat has entrusted the future.<UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
The brands are ready, I presume? Excellent. With the Loporrits having deployed their supporters, we are ready to proceed.
Let us rejoin Y'shtola posthaste, and prise open our gate unto the void.
This is it...
I have duly informed Y'shtola of our task's completion.
While you all tend to matters in the Thirteenth, I shall remain here and ensure the integrity of gate and seal both.
My thanks for seeing to the supporters. With this, all is in readiness for the ritual.
First, I shall give the order to Alphinaud and Alisaie in the Tower of Babil to channel aether to the moon.
Once we have amassed a sufficient amount of energy, Urianger and I shall begin our incantations to open a voidgate.
If all goes well, a tear will form in the fabric of reality, at which point you must activate the brands and put in place the containment seal.
That is all. If there are no questions, then let us begin!
Zero appears to be lost in thought, her gaze fixed upon the fathomless abyss...
My lance will be ready should any more of Golbez's pawns appear.
No sign of a watcher or any Loporrits. Perhaps they were swallowed up in the Flood of Darkness...or perhaps they never existed here.
The surface of the moon is a grim shade of crimson. A consequence of the Flood of Darkness perhaps.
No matter how you strain your eyes, you spy no signs of life. In all directions extends a desolate waste without end.
You hold your breath in an attempt to catch the faintest noise. Save for the sounds of your comrades, there is nothing.
So far, you have failed to find any clues as to Azdaja's whereabouts. Perhaps Zero has noticed something you missed...
